              "text": "This method is called after the dialog is visually closed and gives an opportunity for doing clean up. The dialog lifecycle completes after closing and there should be no resources left inside the object. Even though the dialog may be revived again for a new lifecycle using show() method, this is considered a whole new lifecycle that should reallocate its own resources. If there are any resources that you would like to keep for multiple lifecycles, consider allocating it outside the dialog object and passing its reference to the dialog constructor."
